Model Specific Description: This field is used to indicate an identifier attributed to the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the type of an identifier attributed to the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the provider of the identifier attributed to the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the source based on which the identifier was attributed to the object.
This field is used to indicate the main name attributed to the documented group. No part break down of name is here implied. The full name of a group is expected here where available.
This field is used to indicate the language of the name attributed to the documented entity.
This field is used to indicate a general type assigned to the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the legal status of the documented group.
This field is used to indicate additional names under which the documented group is known. This can be linked to the additional name type and earliest and latest date of use of that name.
This field is used to indicate the type of alternate name that is attributed to the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the language of the alternate name attributed to the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the earliest known date for use of this name for the documented group.
This field is used to indicate the latest known date for use of this name for the documented group.
This field is used to record the group or individual attributing the alternative name to the documented group.
This field is used to record the source on the basis of which the organization attributing the alternative name use based their attribution.
